            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "To all the parants, never take admission in Gaur international school.\n\n1:-School is forcing parants to make quarterly payments in the middle of the year.\n2:-School is increasing fee every year.\n3:-School administration has do not care attitude.\n4:-Only sanskrit language option.\n5:- No invitation to parants for the Annual Function, unless you pay 1500rs.\n6:-Academics not properly followed.\n7:-NCRT test book which parants purchase is costing around 7700+rs. class 7th, and most of the books are not even used.\n8:-Bus fee is 3000+rs. every month, and they dont switch on the AC in the bus during morning.\n\nOver all its a waste of money as this is a builder's school with no ethics.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
